A new miniseries spotlighting the mysterious golden-helmeted hero from the JSA! Hector Hall moves to Salem, Massachusetts in an effort to lead a normal life...but when Caitlin Bibeau and her angry ex-boyfriend come to town, they bring with them a centuries-old evil that dates back to ancient Egypt!
name: The Curse, Part 1

description: The action-packed mystical miniseries continues! Nabu has disappeared and Dr. Fate grows ever more alarmed at his absence as the coven of Salem mystics make their magical intentions known. Meanwhile, Justin Guilder's life takes a turn for the worse as Nabu's ancient enemy, The Curse, reappears with a vengeance seeking to destroy Dr. Fate!
name: The Curse, Part 2

description: The solo adventures of Dr. Fate continue! Nabu has disappeared, and Dr. Fate grows more alarmed at his absence and the coven of Salem mystics make their magical intentions known. Meanwhile, Justin Guilder's life takes a turn for the worse as Nabu's ancient enemy, The Curse, reappears with a vengeance seeking to destroy Fate and all of Salem with the help of the infernal demons he calls Skynts!
name: The Curse, Part 3

description: The situation in Salem has gone from worse to Apocalyptic as the evil influence of The Curse spreads! The Tower of Fate has fallen into the hands of a servant of Chaos, and so has the beautiful Caitln Bibeau. Salem's mystics do everything in their power to contain the evil, but will it be enough to stem the tide of horror as Doctor Fate lies broken and bleeding, his destruction near at hand!
name: The Curse, Part 4

description: The startling conclusion to the 5-issue miniseries! Nabu has always expressed doubts about Hector Hall's worthiness to bear the mantle of Fate. Now, pitted against an enemy even Nabu fears, with the lives of his friends and perhaps the world in balance, it's time to find out if Doctor Fate can do what must be done.
name: The Curse, Part 5

description: Marvel's Most Wanted - the villains-turned-would-be-heroes known as the Thunderbolts - are back! But which side of the law are they on this time? If they're up to their old villainous ways, the Avengers are determined to find out about it - and stop them before they get started! But which side is Hawkeye on?
name: The Cause of Justice

description: When the Avengers can't stop the radioactive Cobalt Man from going nuclear, the Thunderbolts swoop in on cleanup duty by recruiting him into their ranks! Will the teams withstand this high-tension standoff? Can the Thunderbolts even be trusted? And who IS the mysterious Cobalt Man?
name: The Fine Line

description: Has an Avenger infiltrated the T-Bolts' team? Do the T-Bolts have a mole of their own inside the Avengers? And which character is mad as hell and just can't take it anymore?
name: Nerves

description: Secrets revealed! Schemes undone! Loyalties betrayed! And the way one character deals with the emotional maelstrom could very will lead to the destruction of both teams!
name: Betrayal

description: How can they be trusted to save the world when it turns out that they couldn't trust each other? With their greatest plan in ruins around them, their greatest fears are exposed. Will it bring the Thunderbolts together, or finally tear them apart?
name: Truth and Concequences

description: A tragic conflict! A fateful decision! A team torn apart! The lives of both teams are changed and the ramifications will affect the characters for years to come. Will the tragic conclusion to the Limited Series mark the end of the Thunderbolts... or a new beginning?
name: Blood Will Tell

description:
Emmet Proudhawk is a telepath who was hired by the C.I.A. to find a bunch of teenage kids who have all been known to have a psychic ability. He would find them, but on his routine follow up, Proudhawk would discover the children dead. Wanting to save as many as he can, Proudhawk stays one step ahead of the C.I. A. and is able to rescue five of the kids. In hopes that together they would have a chance to survive.

Notes:

  • This issue appears in the 1986 movie Firewalker.
name: Hour of the Wolf

description: In this issue the five kids who make up tghe Psi Force team are trying to make it back to the sanctuary while carrying Emmet Proudhawks dead body, after the events of the first issue. They soon find out that they are being chased by both the local and federal authorities.
name: Sanctuary

description: The gang goes to school for the first time together. A kid sees them summon the Psi-Hawk, and attacks them later on the next day. Wayne tries to run away but is forced to go back by a unseen force. Wayne figures out that Psi-Hawk is keeping them all together with force.
name: Warriors

description: Kathy figured how to beat the Psi-Hawk and go back home. But Psi-Hawk has been making the others miserible. So they go to Kathy and convinces Kathy to come back to the sanctuary.
name: Going Home

description: A new paranormal is in the picture Thomas Boyd. He is sent to capture and if needed kill Psi-force. While anastasia is having internal problems with when to use her powers. But with the help of Anastasia's healing powers she defeats him, but he got away.
name: The Touch

description: Tis the season to be jolly. However, the members of Psi Force have little to be happy about. Tyrone is feeling home sick. He uses his abilities to visit home. He finds out all is not well at home. Meanwhile, a few thugs have taken Tyrone's body.
name: ...Where The Heart Is.

description: The team arrives in Seattle. However, they run afoul of a local pimp. Crawley finally reaches his breaking point and takes drastic action.
name: Deadly Piper

description:
Stalker has returned after his defeat at the hands of Anastasia. He attacks the group during a tour of Alcatraz. The team forms Psi-Hawk. However, Wayne is weakened and Anastasia isunconscious. Stalker is able to defeat Psi-Hawk.
However, as Stalker's employers come to collect the team, he begins to see the error of his ways. Tyrone and Anastasia are able to call Psi-Hawk. Stalker concentrates on the medallion and adds his power. However, after the battle is won, he runs off to do some soul searching.
name: Trapped

description: Wayne wrestles with hisconscious. Can he come to grips with internal conflict? Who will step up to help Wayne in his time of need? The answer may surprise you.
name: Pushed Too Far

description: The kids head to an Apache Reservation and learn more about themselves and the mighty spirit - the Psi-Hawk.
name: The Searchers

description: The kids continue to learn more about the nature of their abilities, but when the team gets trapped in the mines its up to Wayne to help them before its too late. Plus, the teams mysterious pursuer is finally revealed.
The kids must overcome their fears and confront an extortionist that takes money from parents for the safety of their runaways.
When a diplomat hides behind his diplomatic immunity to kidnap Stasi, its up to Psi-Force to save the day.
When Tyrones body is abducted the team sets out to find him. But when Stalker goes berserk will Psi-Force even be enough to stop him?
Michael Crawley is tired of running and hiding. He arrives at the Clinic and comes face-to-face with the paranormal heroes of DP-7.
When the kids learn about what the Foundation has in store foe them they make an escape, but the company isnt going to let them go quietly.
